name: float_f32_positive_infinity
description: |
  Positive infinity is a valid IEEE 754 binary32 value rather than a finite
  number or a NaN. It tests parsers and serializers that reject non-finite
  values, range checks that only compare against a maximum, and arithmetic such
  as infinity minus infinity that produces NaN.
format: hex
decode-as: f32-le
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "infinity"
  - "non-finite"
---
00 00 80 7f   # 0x7f800000: +infinity
